      <p>
        Privly is about creating a square deal for users, and that can't be done with a closed-source, proprietary platform. Privacy on the internet is not something that can--or should--be owned. The lead developer of the Privly project, <%= link_to "Sean McGregor", "http://www.privly.org/content/sean-mcgregor" %>, is recruiting leaders for a <%= link_to "Kickstarter", "http://www.kickstarter.com/projects/229630898/protect-your-content-anywhere-on-the-web-privly" %> seeded foundation dedicated to protecting the Privly source code. Anyone can add their skills to the project and their contribution will be protected.
        <br/>
        <br/>
        In addition to the foundation, <%= link_to "Sean", "http://www.privly.org/content/sean-mcgregor" %> is forming an unaffiliated for-profit entity to be a default whitelisted host in the Privly network (read: <%= link_to "Why a Privly Server", "http://www.privly.org/content/why-privly-server" %>). By enforcing the strictest standards of privacy on whitelisted hosts, we hope to change the incentives of web companies to proactively protect user privacy.
        <br/>
        <br/>
        We are still in the early stages of development, so there will never be a better time to <%= link_to "join", pages_join_path %>.
      </p>
